Package team2869.bethpage.robotics.aerialassist.commands

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AutonomousDrive
    Command that drives the robot forward, at a slight diagonal, in autonomous mode, while winding the shooter mechanism.
    AutonomousShootBall
    CommandGroup that creates a sequence of commands to run during autonomous.
    CommandBase
    The base for all commands.
    DriveToExactClick
    Often the robot may be positioned by the operator so that the target power is between two integer click values.
    HalfDrive
    Command that drives the robot at half speed, in any direction, and this may be used for careful maneuvering of the robot.
    InvertedDrive
    Command that inverts the orientation of the robot, and is quite a deal more intuitive than spinning the robot around.
    MecanumDrive
    Default Command that constantly runs on the driveTrain subsytem until another Command replaces it.
    ResetShoot
    Command that resets the launcher subsystem after a shot has been completed.
    Shoot
    Command that shoots the ball after winding has been completed.
    ShootBall
    CommandGroup that creates a sequence of commands to run during teleoperated game mode.
    SpinDrive
    Command that allows the robot to spin without the use of the secondary joystick's x axis, by converting the primary joystick's x axis into the rotation axis.
    StopDrive
    Stops the movement of the robot's driveTrain.
    StopRobot
    Stops all of the robot's functions, in order to act as a timeout during autonomous.
    TurnDrive
    Command that implements all set turn functionalities for the robot, by allowing it to turn in any direction and for a set amount of time.
    WinderLaunch
    Default Command that constantly runs on the launcher subsystem until another Command replaces it.
